rComments: He clearly cares about his students and wants us to do well and be interested and engaged. He's kind of meh at lecturing, but he puts so much effort into making interesting, visual based assignments that i learned more from than any other basic essay. This is architecture/art school, if u don't want to learn through visual mediums, leave.

His class was a mess. There was no clear takeaway from any lecture, most of it was review and elementary subject matter. He assigned massive studio projects. We received not 1 word of feedback all semester. And he tasked us with evaluating SideWalk Labs, which he was contracted by... do your own work prof.

As a new professor, he doesn't seems know what he suppose to do and as a reading lecture course he gives studio homework. But he clearly dont know what he is expecting. And it is sad that it is difficult to catch the main arguement in his lecture content...
